[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Maintainers: How to Update and Publish[m
 [m
[31m-- `./scripts/publish-github-packages.bat` prompts for GitHub credentials and runs `gradlew publish` to GitHub Packages (for development or JitPack). The vendor JSON currently points at Maven Central.[m
[31m-- GitHub Actions workflows:[m
[31m-  - `.github/workflows/update-vendor-json.yml` updates `absolutelib.json` version and JSON URL when a `v*` tag is pushed.[m
[31m-  - `.github/workflows/pages.yml` deploys `absolutelib.json` to GitHub Pages at `https://team4308.github.io/absolutelib/absolutelib.json`.[m
[32m+[m[32mThis section is for people maintaining the library.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 1. Version bump[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Update the Gradle project version:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```properties[m
[32m+[m[32m   // gradle.properties[m
[32m+[m[32m   group=ca.team4308[m
[32m+[m[32m   version=1.0.X[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Update the vendordep JSON version and dependency:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```json[m
[32m+[m[32m   // absolutelib.json[m
[32m+[m[32m   "version": "1.0.X",[m
[32m+[m[32m   "javaDependencies": [[m
[32m+[m[32m     {[m
[32m+[m[32m       "groupId": "ca.team4308",[m
[32m+[m[32m       "artifactId": "absolutelib-java",[m
[32m+[m[32m       "version": "1.0.X"[m
[32m+[m[32m     }[m
[32m+[m[32m   ][m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Update the README examples to match the new version:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```gradle[m
[32m+[m[32m   implementation "ca.team4308:absolutelib-java:1.0.4"[m
[32m+[m[32m   implementation "com.github.Team4308:absolutelib:1.0.4"[m
[32m+[m[32m   ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 2. Publishing the Java artifact[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThere are two publishing paths:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- GitHub Packages (for internal use / debug)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Self-hosted Maven under GitHub Pages (for vendordep)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### GitHub Packages[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFrom the `absolutelib` root:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```powershell[m
[32m+[m[32mscripts\publish-github-packages.bat[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe script:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Prompts for your GitHub username and a PAT with `read:packages`, `write:packages`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Runs `gradlew verifyPublishCreds` and then `gradlew publish`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Uses the `GitHubPackages` repository block in `build.gradle` to upload.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIf you get a 409 conflict, the version already exists; bump `version` in `gradle.properties` if you really need a new build.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m#### Self-hosted Maven (GitHub Pages)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis is handled by the `pages.yml` workflow:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- It runs on pushes to `main` and tags `v*`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- It calls:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m  ```bash[m
[32m+[m[32m  ./gradlew -Pversion="${PUBLISH_VERSION}" -PpagesPublish publishPagesRepo[m
[32m+[m[32m  ```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- `publishPagesRepo`:[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Publishes the `absolutelib-java` artifact into `build/pages-maven` using the `GitHubPagesLocal` Maven repository.[m
[32m+[m[32m  - Generates a minimal HTML index.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- The workflow then copies `build/pages-maven` to `deploy/releases` and deploys it via `actions/deploy-pages`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mResult: `https://team4308.github.io/absolutelib/releases` is a standard Maven repo the vendordep and robot projects can use without credentials.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 3. Tagging and vendor JSON auto-update[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThe `.github/workflows/update-vendor-json.yml` workflow runs when you push a tag `v*`:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Extracts the version from the tag name (e.g. `v1.0.2` â†’ `1.0.2`).[m
[32m+[m[32m- Updates the `"version"` field in `absolutelib.json`.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Updates the `jsonUrl` to point at the tagged version on raw.githubusercontent.com (for archival).[m
[32m+[m[32m- Commits and pushes the updated `absolutelib.json`.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mFor the GitHub Pages path (the URL you give to teams), we keep:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```json[m
[32m+[m[32m"jsonUrl": "https://team4308.github.io/absolutelib/absolutelib.json"[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mand the `pages.yml` workflow ensures that is updated on each deploy.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 4. Robot project pattern (example: `tut`)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mIn a robot project like `tut`, the minimal pattern is:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m```groovy[m
[32m+[m[32m// Detect vendordep[m
[32m+[m[32mdef hasAbsoluteLibVendordep = file("vendordeps/absolutelib.json").exists()[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mdependencies {[m
[32m+[m[32m    // WPILib[m
[32m+[m[32m    annotationProcessor wpi.java.deps.wpilibAnnotations()[m
[32m+[m[32m    implementation wpi.java.deps.wpilib()[m
[32m+[m[32m    implementation wpi.java.vendor.java()[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m    // Only use absolutelib if vendordep is installed[m
[32m+[m[32m    if (hasAbsoluteLibVendordep) {[m
[32m+[m[32m        implementation "ca.team4308:absolutelib-java:1.0.4"[m
[32m+[m[32m    }[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mrepositories {[m
[32m+[m[32m    mavenCentral()[m
[32m+[m[32m    maven { url "https://jitpack.io" } // optional extra if using JitPack directly[m
[32m+[m[32m}[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThis makes absolutelib optional: projects without the vendordep still build, ones with the vendordep get the dependency.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m---[m
